.\" Manpage for gamesteam.
.TH GAMESTEAM 1 "2026-07-19" "gamesteam 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gamesteam \- universal, GPU-aware Steam/Proton launch wrapper
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gamesteam
.RI [ options ]
.B %command%
.br
.B gamesteam
.RI [ options ]
.B \-\-
.I command
.br
.B gamesteam
.BR \-\-list\-gpus " | " \-\-help " | " \-\-version
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gamesteam
is a launch wrapper for Steam/Proton games. With no options it detects the
available GPUs, prefers the discrete one, applies vendor-correct device
selection and Proton/DXVK/VKD3D tuning, runs the game under
.BR gamemoderun ,
and switches the system to a performance power profile for the session
(restored on exit). For integrated GPUs it also wraps the game in a
native-resolution
.BR gamescope (1)
compositor with FSR upscaling; discrete GPUs render natively.
.PP
It is intended for Steam's per-game or global launch options:
.PP
.RS
.B gamesteam %command%
.RE
.PP
Every external tool is probed at runtime and skipped when absent, so the same
script runs on any Linux distribution. GPUs and displays are read from
.IR sysfs ;
no
.BR lspci (8)
is required.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS GPU
.TP
.BR \-g ", " \-\-graphics " " \fItarget\fR
Select which GPU to render on. Default:
.BR auto .
.I target
is one of
.BR auto ", " discrete ", " integrated ", " nvidia ", " amd ", " intel ", "
.BR integrated\-intel ", " integrated\-amd .
.TP
.B \-\-force\-discrete
Alias for
.BR "\-g discrete" .
.TP
.B \-\-force\-integrated
Alias for
.BR "\-g integrated" .
.TP
.B \-\-list\-gpus
Print the detected GPUs (index, vendor, PCI address, type, boot_vga) and exit.
.SS gamescope
By default gamescope is enabled automatically for integrated GPUs, where
reducing the internal render resolution and FSR-upscaling to native is the
biggest performance win, and left off for discrete GPUs, which render at native
resolution. The options in this section apply only when gamescope is active.
.TP
.B \-\-gamescope
Always run the game inside a native-resolution gamescope compositor.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-gamescope
Never use gamescope.
.TP
.BR \-\-res " " \fIWxH\fR
gamescope output resolution. Default: auto-detect the connected display's
native resolution.
.TP
.BR \-\-refresh " " \fIHz\fR
Refresh-rate cap. Default: the display's native refresh.
.TP
.BR \-\-render\-scale " " \fIfactor\fR
Internal render scale, 0.1 to 1.0. Default: 1.0 for discrete GPUs, 0.75 for
integrated. A value below 1.0 enables FSR upscaling to the output resolution.
.TP
.B \-\-native
Render at the output resolution with no upscaling (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-render\-scale 1.0" ).
.TP
.BR \-\-fsr ", " \-\-no\-fsr
Force FSR upscaling on or off.
.TP
.B \-\-hdr
Enable HDR output.
.SS System
.TP
.B \-\-gamemode
Wrap the game in
.BR gamemoderun .
Default: on when gamemode is available.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-gamemode
Do not use gamemode.
.TP
.BR \-\-power\-profile " " \fIname\fR
Switch to power profile
.I name
for the session (restored on exit). Default:
.BR performance .
Typical names:
.BR performance ", " balanced ", " power\-saver .
.TP
.B \-\-no\-power\-profile
Leave the power profile unchanged.
.TP
.BR \-\-hud ", " \-\-no\-hud
Enable or disable the MangoHud overlay. Default: off, or on if
.B MANGOHUD=1
is set in the environment.
.SS Tuning
.TP
.B \-\-cachyos
Apply CachyOS-Proton tuning.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-cachyos
Disable CachyOS tuning. Default: auto-detect (see
.BR NOTES ).
.SS General
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Print the resolved plan (detected GPUs, selection, environment, final command)
and exit without launching anything.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Explain detection and decisions on standard error.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress warnings.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show the version and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MANGOHUD
If set to a non-zero value, start with the MangoHud overlay (same as
.BR \-\-hud ).
.TP
.B GAMESTEAM_SYSFS
Directory to read GPUs and displays from instead of
.IR /sys .
Intended for testing.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/gamesteam/config
System-wide default options.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/gamesteam/config
Per-user default options (defaults to
.IR ~/.config/gamesteam/config ).
.PP
Both files are shell fragments that set the option variables (for example
.BR "GRAPHICS=nvidia" " or " "USE_GAMESCOPE=on" ).
Command-line flags always override them.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B gamesteam %command%
Auto-detect, render on the discrete GPU, run under gamemode.
.TP
.B gamesteam \-g nvidia \-\-gamescope %command%
Force the NVIDIA GPU and wrap the game in gamescope.
.TP
.B gamesteam \-\-force\-integrated \-\-gamescope \-\-render\-scale 0.7 %command%
Use the integrated GPU, rendering at 70% and FSR-upscaling to native.
.TP
.B gamesteam \-\-no\-power\-profile \-\-no\-gamemode %command%
Apply only the GPU/Proton environment.
.TP
.B gamesteam \-n \-v \-\- /bin/true
Print the plan for the current machine without launching anything.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success (including
.BR \-\-help ", " \-\-version ", " \-\-list\-gpus ", and " \-\-dry\-run ),
or the exit status of the launched command.
.TP
.B 1
A usage error or a failed prerequisite.
.SH NOTES
PROTON_* and VKD3D_* tuning takes effect on Proton-CachyOS or Proton-GE; stock
Valve Proton ignores the CachyOS-specific variables harmlessly.
.PP
CachyOS mode is auto-detected via
.IR /etc/os-release ,
a
.RB * \-cachyos
kernel, or a
.B game\-performance
binary, so it also activates on a non-CachyOS host running the CachyOS kernel.
.PP
gamescope
.B \-\-adaptive\-sync
(VRR) only passes through when nested if the parent compositor has VRR enabled.
NVIDIA with gamescope needs a recent driver (>= 555). Intel Arc (discrete) is
not auto-distinguished from an Intel iGPU; use
.B \-g intel
to select it regardless.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gamescope (1),
.BR gamemoderun (1),
.BR mangohud (1),
.BR powerprofilesctl (1)
